Date: Fri, 21 Jul 2000 14:25:13 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Boston Globe via Associated Press, 21 Jul 2000 11:32 [edited

Orange County discovers a mosquito with West Nile virus
--------------------------------------------------------
A mosquito carrying the West Nile virus has been found in Orange County,
officials said. The county now plans to drop larvicide to kill mosquito
[larvae in all of the county's 20 000 municipal storm drains as soon as
next week and to distribute about 30 000 containers of free insect
repellent through local pharmacies.
The mosquito was one of 11 captured July 11 by a trap in the town of
Minisink. Results of the test on a type of mosquito, the day-flying _Aedes
japonicus_, came back late Wednesday. Finding the disease in the less
numerous and rural _Aedes japonicus_ means there is a good chance West Nile
virus will show up in the much more common _Culex pipiens_ house mosquito,
said county Health Commissioner Dr. Maxcy Smith. For now, County Executive
Joseph Rampe doesn't favor spraying the rural habitat of _Aedes japonicus_
with pesticides.
